item.content:encoded: I just read that consumers have boosted the economy. Honestly, that's no surprise to me. As a consumer, I see how tariffs are basically killing us with extra taxes 💸, and with AI driving up component prices 🤖 and causing shortages 🚫, I've sped up my buying 🛒. If tariffs keep climbing, prices keep rising, and PC parts keep vanishing, 2026 is going to look pretty bleak for us consumers 😟.
